<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-09-13T09:24:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-09-13T09:24:00-05:00" n="789" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d789">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">760i.61/19: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Commissioner at Riga</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Young</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-09-13T16:00:00+01:36"><hi rend="italic">September
                                            13, 1920—4 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received September
                                    14—12:30 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>151. Your September 11th, 6 p.m. Instruction complied with. Though
                                without any evidence or proof, it is my opinion that inquiry
                                regarding our naval vessels emanates from Bolsheviks. Inquiry
                                regarding consul apparently purely Esthonian.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Young</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>